Data model (fields)

id: integer
name: string
description: string
target_date: string (YYYY-MM-DD)
status: string ("Not Started" | "In Progress" | "Completed")
created_at: string (timestamp)
API endpoints (must have all four CRUD methods)

POST /api/courses
Create a new course
Body: { name, description, target_date, status? }
Response: 201 with created course
GET /api/courses
List all courses
Response: 200 with array of courses
GET /api/courses/<id>
Retrieve one course
Response: 200 with course or 404 if not found
PUT /api/courses/<id>
Full update of a course (all fields required)
Body: { name, description, target_date, status }
Response: 200 with updated course or 404
DELETE /api/courses/<id>
Delete a course
Response: 200 with message or 404 Optional bonus endpoints (optional, for practice)
GET /api/courses/stats
Basic stats (e.g., count by status)
GET /api/courses/search?q=term
Simple text search in name/description
Storage with JSON (how to store/retrieve)

File: data/courses.json
If missing, create with []
Load on each request (read)
Save after create/update/delete (write)
Helper ideas (in app.py):
load_courses(): read and return list
save_courses(courses): write list back to file
get_next_id(courses): max id + 1
Note: simple in-file storage; no concurrency handling needed for learning, but you can add a small file lock if you see race conditions.
UI plan (basic UI to interact with APIs)

index.html
Simple form to add a course (name, description, target_date, status)
A table/list to display courses
Edit/Delete buttons per row
script.js
fetch POST to /api/courses to create
fetch GET to /api/courses to load
fetch PUT to /api/courses/<id> to update
fetch DELETE to /api/courses/<id> to delete
Update the UI dynamically without page reload
Minimal CSS in styles.css for readability
